Class AbapHardCodedUsernameCheck

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.cqse.check.framework.core.CheckImplementationBase
      • eu.cqse.check.base.HardCodedLiteralsCheckBase
        • eu.cqse.check.abap.AbapHardCodedUsernameCheck

  • @ACheck(name="Hard-coded user name",
        description="Hard-coded user names should be avoided, since hard-coded credentials like user name or password are a potential security risk. In any case it should be avoided that the program flow depends on the name of the currently active user.",
        groupName="Security",
        languages=ABAP,
        defaultEnablement=YELLOW,
        parameters=ABSTRACT_SYNTAX_TREE)
public class AbapHardCodedUsernameCheck
extends HardCodedLiteralsCheckBase
    Checks for hard-coded user names. The check searches for occurrences of character literals which occur in context of an identifier which may indicate the it stores a user name, e.g. variables named like 'user_name', 'user', 'sys_uname', ...
